  "prompt": "How did Harry's get its name?",
  "response": "Harry's, the popular men's grooming brand, got its name from its founders, Jeff Raider and Andy Katz-Mayfield. The name itself is straightforward and approachable, reflecting the brand's mission to offer high-quality, affordable grooming products in a way that feels personal and connected to the customer.\n\nThe founders chose the name \"Harry's\" because it has a classic, timeless quality that aligns with their brand values of simplicity, reliability, and accessibility. It\u2019s a name that feels familiar and trustworthy, much like a friend or neighbor, which fits well with the brand's direct-to-consumer model and community-focused ethos.\n\nWhen Harry's launched in 2013, it aimed to disrupt the traditional razor market by offering a more customer-friendly experience, and the name has played a key role in its identity as a friendly, modern, and dependable brand.",
